      Most fractures heal within weeks — but delayed union and non-union fractures can leave patients in pain for months or years, often being told surgery is the only answer. Bone Marrow Injection therapy offers a powerful non-surgical alternative that stimulates the body's own healing mechanisms at the fracture site.
